6.aspx |title=AFI AWARDS 2016 |publisher=[[American Film Institute]] |date=December 8, 2016 |accessdate=December 8, 2016}}</ref>\n|Television Programs of the Year\n|''Better Call Saul''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=21| 2017\n| rowspan=1|[[74th Golden Globe Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/12/2017-golden-globe-nominations-full-list-74th-golden-globe-awards-1201868543/ |title=Golden Globe Nominations: 'La La Land', 'Moonlight' Lead Films; 'People Vs. OJ' Tops TV |first=Patrick |last=Hipes |publisher=Deadline.com |date=December 12, 2016 |accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n| Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama\n| Bob Odenkirk\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[21st Satellite Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/2016-satellite-awards-nominees-listed-includes-moonlight-la-la-land-950935 |title=Satellite Award Nominees Revealed |first=Gregg |last=Kilday |date=November 29, 2016 |accessdate=November 30, 2016 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pressacademy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/2016-Winners.pdf |title=THE INTERNATIONAL PRESS ACADEMY ANNOUNCES WINNERS FOR THE 21 ANNUAL SATELLITE AWARDS |publisher=International Press Academy |date=December 18, 2016 |accessdate=December 19, 2016}}</ref>\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Television Series \u2013 Drama|Best Drama Series]]\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| Bob Odenkirk\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actor in a Series, Miniseries or TV Film]]\n| Jonathan Banks\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actress in a Series, Miniseries or TV Film]]\n| Rhea Seehorn\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=1|[[Cinema Audio Society Awards 2016|53rd Cinema Audio Society Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170220013321/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2017-cinema-audio-society-sound-mixers-award-winners-970631 |archivedate=February 20, 2017 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2017-cinema-audio-society-sound-mixers-award-winners-970631 |title='La La Land' Wins Cinema Audio Society Award for Sound Mixing |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |first=Carolyn |last=Giardina |date=February 18, 2017 |accessdate=February 19, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for Television Series \u2013 One Hour\n| Phillip W. Palmer, Larry B. Benjamin, Kevin Valentine, Matt Hovland and David Michael Torres (\"Klick\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[Writers Guild of America Awards 2016|69th Writers Guild of America Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wga-tv-nominations-stranger-things-westworld-atlanta-break-through-1201933697/ |title=Writers Guild TV Nominations: 'Stranger Things,' 'Westworld,' 'This Is Us,' 'Atlanta' Break Through |work=Variety |first=Oriana |last=Schwindt |date=December 5, 2016 |accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n| Drama Series\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|Episodic Drama\n| Gordon Smith (\"Gloves-Off\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Heather Marion and Vince Gilligan (\"Klick\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Thomas Schnauz]] (\"[[Switch (Better Call Saul)|Switch]]\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=1|[[Location Managers Guild Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |title='Hidden Figures,' 'La La Land' Among Location Managers Guild Award Nominees |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hidden-figures-la-la-land-location-managers-guild-awards-nominees-2017-978431/item/outstanding-locations-a-contemporary-tv-series-location-managers-guild-award-nominees-2017-978 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Carolyn |last=Giardina |date=February 22, 2017 |accessdate=February 26, 2017}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Locations in a Contemporary TV Series\n| Christian Diaz 