Michael |date=August 3, 2019 |accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Achievement in Drama\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[71st Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/16/arts/television/emmy-nominations-list.html |title=Here's a Full List of the 2019 Emmy Nominations |work=The New York Times |first=Sara |last=Aridi |date=July 16, 2019 |accessdate=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Guest Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| Michael McKean\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Music Supervision\n| Thomas Golubi\u0107 (\"Something Stupid\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Sound Editing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One-Hour)|Outstanding Sound Editing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One-Hour)]]\n| Kurt Nicholas Forshager, Kathryn Madsen, Mark Cookson, Matt Temple, Jane Boegel-Koch, Jason Newman, Jeff Cranford and Gregg Barbanell (\"[[Talk (Better Call Saul)|Talk]]\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One-Hour)|Outstanding Sound Mixing for a Comedy or Drama Series (One Hour)]]\n| Larry Benjamin, Kevin Valentine and Phillip W. Palmer (\"Talk\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=5|[[71st Primetime Emmy Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/09/22/emmys-2019-awards-winners-list/ |title=Emmys 2019: Game of Thrones Ties Record and Leads TV Pack; Fleabag, Chernobyl and Mrs. Maisel Win Big |first=Matt Webb |last=Mitovich |website=TVLine |date=September 22, 2019 |accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Drama Series\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series\n| Bob Odenkirk\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series\n| Jonathan Banks\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Giancarlo Esposito\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Writing for a Drama Series\n| Thomas Schnauz & Peter Gould (\"Winner\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[45th Saturn Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mancuso |first1=Vinnie |title='Avengers: Endgame', 'Game of Thrones' Lead the 2019 Saturn Awards Nominations |url=https://collider.com/saturn-awards-nominations-2019/ |website=Collider |accessdate=July 17, 2019 |date=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n| Best Action-Thriller Television Series\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor on a Television Series\n| Jonathan Banks\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actress on a Television Series\n| Rhea Seehorn\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Guest-Starring Performance on a Television Series\n| Rainer Bock\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|2019 Gold Derby Awards<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/gold-derby-tv-awards-2019-nominations-game-of-thrones-veep-news/ |title=Gold Derby TV Awards 2019 nominations: 'Game of Thrones' and 'Veep' lead, while 'Pose' is the top new show of the year |date=July 24, 2019 |publisher=[[Gold Derby]] |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref>\n| Best Drama Series\n| ''Better Call Saul''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Actor\n| Bob Odenkirk\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Supporting Actor\n| Jonathan Banks\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Supporting Actress\n| Rhea Seehorn\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Guest Actor\n| Michael McKean\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_rank         = y\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n| hide_tv_season    = y\n\n| link1             = Better Call Saul (season 1)\n| timeslot1         = Sunday 10:00 pm (premiere)<br />Monday 10:00 pm\n| timeslot_length1  = 1\n| episodes1         = 10\n| start1            = February 8, 2015\n| startrating1      = 6.88<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/02/10/sunday-cable-ratings-the-walking-dead-tops-night-better-call-saul-talking-dead-the-real-housewives-of-atlanta-more/361257/ |title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'The Walking Dead' Tops Night + 'Better Call Saul', 'Talking Dead', 'The Real Housewives of Atlanta' &